...
9 | make_mutable!(self); | -------------------- in this macro invocation | = note: `mut` may be followed by `variable` and `variable @ pattern` 所以说，宏在匹配的时候，会欣然把 self 当作标识符接受，进而允许你把 self 带到那些实际上没办法使用的情况中去。但是，也成吧，既然得同时记住 self 既是关键词又是标识符，那下面这个讲道理应该可行，对吧？ macro_rules! make_self_mutable { ($i:ident) => {let mut $i = self;};
} struct Dummy(i32); impl Dummy { fn double(self) -> Dummy { make_self_mutable!(mut_self); mut_self.0 *= 2; mut_self }
} fn main() { println!("{:?}", Dummy(4).double().0);
} 实际上也不行，编译错误变成： error[E0424]: expected value, found module `self` --> src/main.rs:2:33 |
